Note:
C++ Parser - Builds Abstract Syntax Tree from C++ tokens

This file implements a recursive descent parser for the C++ programming language.
Parses C++17 standard syntax including classes, templates, namespaces, lambda
expressions, auto keyword, range-based for loops, and all C++ specific features.

AST Node Types:
- CPP_PROGRAM: Root node containing all declarations
- CPP_CLASS: Class declaration/definition
- CPP_NAMESPACE: Namespace declaration
- CPP_TEMPLATE: Template declaration
- CPP_FUNCTION: Function declaration/definition (including methods)
- CPP_VARIABLE: Variable declaration
- CPP_TYPEDEF: Type alias declaration
- CPP_ENUM: Enum/enum class declaration
- CPP_LAMBDA: Lambda expression
- CPP_STATEMENT: Statement nodes (if, while, for, try-catch, etc.)
- CPP_EXPRESSION: Expression nodes (new, delete, cast, etc.)
- CPP_TYPE: Type information (including template types)

Dependencies:
- cpp_lexer.runa
- compiler/frontend/primitives/memory/layout.runa
- compiler/frontend/primitives/core/string_core.runa
- compiler/frontend/primitives/collections/list.runa
:End Note

Import "compiler/middle/gungnir/hir/translation/frontends/cpp/cpp_lexer.runa" as Lexer
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/memory/layout.runa" as Layout
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/core/string_core.runa" as StringCore
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/collections/list.runa" as List

Note: ============================================================================
Note: AST Node Type Constants
Note: ============================================================================

Constant CPP_PROGRAM as Integer is 1
Constant CPP_CLASS as Integer is 2
Constant CPP_NAMESPACE as Integer is 3
Constant CPP_TEMPLATE as Integer is 4
Constant CPP_FUNCTION as Integer is 5
Constant CPP_VARIABLE as Integer is 6
Constant CPP_TYPEDEF as Integer is 7
Constant CPP_ENUM as Integer is 8
Constant CPP_LAMBDA as Integer is 9

Note: Class-specific nodes
Constant CPP_ACCESS_SPECIFIER as Integer is 15  Note: public, private, protected
Constant CPP_CONSTRUCTOR as Integer is 16
Constant CPP_DESTRUCTOR as Integer is 17
Constant CPP_OPERATOR_OVERLOAD as Integer is 18
Constant CPP_INHERITANCE as Integer is 19

Note: Template nodes
Constant CPP_TEMPLATE_PARAM as Integer is 25
Constant CPP_TEMPLATE_SPECIALIZATION as Integer is 26
Constant CPP_TEMPLATE_INSTANTIATION as Integer is 27

Note: Statement types
Constant CPP_COMPOUND_STMT as Integer is 30
Constant CPP_IF_STMT as Integer is 31
Constant CPP_WHILE_STMT as Integer is 32
Constant CPP_FOR_STMT as Integer is 33
Constant CPP_RANGE_FOR_STMT as Integer is 34  Note: C++11 range-based for
Constant CPP_DO_WHILE_STMT as Integer is 35
Constant CPP_SWITCH_STMT as Integer is 36
Constant CPP_CASE_STMT as Integer is 37
Constant CPP_DEFAULT_STMT as Integer is 38
Constant CPP_RETURN_STMT as Integer is 39
Constant CPP_BREAK_STMT as Integer is 40
Constant CPP_CONTINUE_STMT as Integer is 41
Constant CPP_GOTO_STMT as Integer is 42
Constant CPP_LABEL_STMT as Integer is 43
Constant CPP_EXPR_STMT as Integer is 44
Constant CPP_TRY_STMT as Integer is 45
Constant CPP_CATCH_STMT as Integer is 46
Constant CPP_THROW_STMT as Integer is 47

Note: Expression types
Constant CPP_BINARY_EXPR as Integer is 50
Constant CPP_UNARY_EXPR as Integer is 51
Constant CPP_CALL_EXPR as Integer is 52
Constant CPP_SUBSCRIPT_EXPR as Integer is 53
Constant CPP_MEMBER_EXPR as Integer is 54
Constant CPP_ARROW_EXPR as Integer is 55
Constant CPP_CAST_EXPR as Integer is 56
Constant CPP_SIZEOF_EXPR as Integer is 57
Constant CPP_TERNARY_EXPR as Integer is 58
Constant CPP_LITERAL_EXPR as Integer is 59
Constant CPP_IDENTIFIER_EXPR as Integer is 60
Constant CPP_ASSIGN_EXPR as Integer is 61
Constant CPP_NEW_EXPR as Integer is 62
Constant CPP_DELETE_EXPR as Integer is 63
Constant CPP_THIS_EXPR as Integer is 64
Constant CPP_SCOPE_RESOLUTION as Integer is 65  Note: ::

Note: Type nodes
Constant CPP_TYPE_NODE as Integer is 70
Constant CPP_POINTER_TYPE as Integer is 71
Constant CPP_REFERENCE_TYPE as Integer is 72
Constant CPP_ARRAY_TYPE as Integer is 73
Constant CPP_FUNCTION_TYPE as Integer is 74
Constant CPP_TEMPLATE_TYPE as Integer is 75
Constant CPP_AUTO_TYPE as Integer is 76  Note: C++11 auto keyword

Note: ============================================================================
Note: AST Node Structure
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning:
A single AST node type covers expressions, statements, declarations, and
type specifiers because C++ uses many of the same operators across all four
families (e.g. ::, ->, .). node_type disambiguates the role; name/value/
type_info/children/attributes/template_params are populated selectively.
line/column come straight from the lexer so diagnostics can quote source.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
72-byte record (9 x i64) at offsets 0..64: node_type (CPP_* constant), name
(StringCore identifier or 0), value (StringCore literal/operator or 0),
type_info (CppASTNode* of declared type or 0), children (List of CppASTNode*
or 0 for leaves), attributes (packed bitfield: access level, virtual,
static, const), template_params (List of CppASTNode* for template-typed
nodes), line, column.
@End Implementation

Type called "CppASTNode":
    node_type as Integer       Note: Node type constant
    name as Integer           Note: Name/identifier (if applicable)
    value as Integer          Note: Value/operator (if applicable)
    type_info as Integer      Note: Type information node
    children as Integer       Note: List of child nodes
    attributes as Integer     Note: Additional attributes (access, template params, etc.)
    template_params as Integer Note: Template parameters (for templates)
    line as Integer          Note: Source line number
    column as Integer        Note: Source column number
End Type

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Parser State
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning:
C++ parsing is context-sensitive: foo<int>::bar means template-id only when
foo is a template, otherwise the < is a less-than. current_class is needed
for access-control checks during member parsing, template_depth disambiguates
nested templates and rules out angle-bracket parsing of "<<" as shift.
error_message + has_error provide sticky first-error reporting consistent
with the semantic analyzer.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
48-byte record (6 x i64) at offsets 0..40: lexer (CppLexer handle),
current_token (token type integer, refreshed on advance_token),
error_message (owned StringCore or 0), has_error (sticky 0/1),
current_class (CppASTNode* of enclosing class declaration or 0),
template_depth (count incremented when entering '<' template arg list,
decremented on '>').
@End Implementation

Type called "CppParser":
    lexer as Integer          Note: C++ lexer
    current_token as Integer  Note: Current token type
    error_message as Integer  Note: Error message (if any)
    has_error as Integer      Note: Boolean: 1 if error occurred
    current_class as Integer  Note: Current class being parsed (for access control)
    template_depth as Integer Note: Template nesting depth
End Type

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Parser Creation and Destruction
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning:
Allocates the 48-byte CppParser record and constructs the underlying
CppLexer. The parser stays decoupled from any global lexer state so
multiple parsers may run concurrently against different sources.
template_depth and current_class are zero-initialised so first-level
declarations behave as non-template, no-enclosing-class context.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Layout.allocate(48); OOM returns 0. Calls Lexer.create_cpp_lexer with
the source; if that fails the partially-built parser is freed and 0 is
returned so the caller observes a single failure point. Writes the
lexer handle (offset 0), zero current_token (refreshed by the priming
advance_token below), 0 error_message/has_error (clean state), 0
current_class (top-level), 0 template_depth. Calling advance_token at
the end primes the cursor so peek_token_type works immediately.
@End Implementation
Process called "create_cpp_parser" takes source as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Create C++ parser from source code

    @Reasoning:
    Initialize parser state including lexer, error tracking, and C++-specific
    context like template depth and current class for proper scoping.
    @End Reasoning

    Let parser_size be 48  Note: CppParser: 6 fields × 8 bytes
    Let parser be proc allocate from Layout with parser_size

    If parser is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let lexer be proc create_cpp_lexer from Lexer with source

    If lexer is equal to 0:
        proc deallocate from Layout with parser
        Return 0
    End If

    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with parser, 0, lexer
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with parser, 8, 0   Note: current_token
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with parser, 16, 0  Note: error_message
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with parser, 24, 0  Note: has_error = false
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with parser, 32, 0  Note: current_class = null
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with parser, 40, 0  Note: template_depth = 0

    Note: Prime the parser with first token
    proc advance_token from parser

    Return parser
End Process

@Reasoning:
Symmetric teardown for create_cpp_parser. Owns the lexer (created during
create) and any error_message string allocated by set_parse_error; the
caller never frees those resources directly. AST nodes produced by the
parser are independent of this lifetime - they survive parser
destruction.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Null parser handle short-circuits with success so paired create/destroy
is safe after an OOM-failed create. Reads lexer handle from offset 0
and delegates to Lexer.destroy_cpp_lexer if non-zero. Reads
error_message from offset 16; frees only if non-zero so a clean parser
doesn't double-free. Finally releases the 48-byte record. Returns 1.
@End Implementation
Process called "destroy_cpp_parser" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Destroy C++ parser and free resources

    If parser is equal to 0:
        Return 1
    End If

    Let lexer be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with parser, 0

    If lexer is not equal to 0:
        proc destroy_cpp_lexer from Lexer with lexer
    End If

    Let error_message be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with parser, 16

    If error_message is not equal to 0:
        proc deallocate from Layout with error_message
    End If

    proc deallocate from Layout with parser

    Return 1
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: AST Node Creation
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning:
Centralised AST node allocator so every parser path produces nodes with the
same zero-initialised slot layout; this lets later passes assume "0 ==
unset" for every slot without per-call resets. Allocation failure returns 0
(parent should propagate fatal).
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Allocates a 72-byte block, writes node_type at offset 0, zeroes the
remaining eight slots (name, value, type_info, children, attributes,
template_params, line, column). Caller is expected to populate line/column
from the lexer immediately after creation; child lists are created lazily
in add_child_to_cpp_ast_node.
@End Implementation

Process called "create_cpp_ast_node" takes node_type as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Create C++ AST node of given type

    Let node_size be 72  Note: CppASTNode: 9 fields × 8 bytes
    Let node be proc allocate from Layout with node_size

    If node is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with node, 0, node_type
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with node, 8, 0   Note: name = null
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with node, 16, 0  Note: value = null
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with node, 24, 0  Note: type_info = null
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with node, 32, 0  Note: children = null
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with node, 40, 0  Note: attributes = null
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with node, 48, 0  Note: template_params = null
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with node, 56, 0  Note: line = 0
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with node, 64, 0  Note: column = 0

    Return node
End Process

@Reasoning:
Children list is created lazily: nodes that never gain children (most
leaves, all literals, plain identifiers) never pay for an empty List.
Allocates the List only when the first child is added.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Null-checks both parent and child (the parser may construct nodes after a
recoverable error). Reads children slot at offset 32; if 0, allocates a
fresh List via create and stores it. Then pushes child onto the list.
Ownership of child transfers to parent's children list.
@End Implementation

Process called "add_child_to_cpp_ast_node" takes parent as Integer, child as Integer:
    Note: Add child node to parent's children list

    If parent is equal to 0:
        Return
    End If

    If child is equal to 0:
        Return
    End If

    Let children be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with parent, 32

    If children is equal to 0:
        Set children to proc create from List
        proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with parent, 32, children
    End If

    proc push from List with children, child
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Token Management
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning:
Single-token-of-lookahead is the canonical parser cursor advance. Caches the
next token type in the parser at offset 8 so peek_token_type is O(1) without
re-invoking the lexer. The lexer itself maintains lexeme/line/column for
the current position; this proc only pulls the integer type.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Loads lexer handle from offset 0, calls Lexer.next_token to refresh state
and obtain the next token-type integer, stores it back at offset 8. The
previous token's lexeme is implicitly discarded by the lexer cursor.
@End Implementation

Process called "advance_token" takes parser as Integer:
    Note: Advance to next token

    Let lexer be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with parser, 0
    Let next_token be proc next_token from Lexer with lexer
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with parser, 8, next_token
End Process

@Reasoning:
Read-only accessor for the current lookahead token-type so recursive-descent
predicates can branch without side effects on the cursor.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Single memory_get_int64 from offset 8. Constant-time, no allocation.
@End Implementation

Process called "peek_token_type" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Get current token type without advancing

    Return proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with parser, 8
End Process

@Reasoning:
The token type is cached on the parser but the lexeme text lives on the
lexer. Identifier/literal parses need the raw text to attach to AST nodes;
this proc bridges to the lexer's current_lexeme accessor without affecting
the lookahead state.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Reads lexer handle from offset 0 and delegates to Lexer.current_lexeme.
Returns a BORROWED pointer into the lexer's internal storage; AST nodes
that want to keep the string must copy it via StringCore.
@End Implementation

Process called "peek_token_lexeme" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Get current token lexeme without advancing

    Let lexer be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with parser, 0
    Return proc current_lexeme from Lexer with lexer
End Process

@Reasoning:
Canonical "match-or-error" combinator used throughout the recursive-descent
parser. Advancing only on match keeps the cursor positioned at the offending
token when an error fires, letting the error recovery layer attempt
synchronisation on the right context.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Compares peek_token_type against expected. Match: advances. Mismatch: calls
set_parse_error with the supplied message; the parser flips has_error=1
sticky and recovery may pick up the broken cursor downstream.
@End Implementation

Process called "expect_token" takes parser as Integer, expected as Integer, message as Integer:
    Note: Expect specific token type or set error

    Let current_type be proc peek_token_type from parser

    If current_type is equal to expected:
        proc advance_token from parser
    Otherwise:
        proc set_parse_error with parser, message
    End If
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Main Parsing Entry Point
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning:
Top-level recursive-descent dispatch. C++ admits a wide menu of file-
scope productions: namespace, class, struct, template, using/typedef,
preprocessor passthrough, function, and global variable. This driver
keeps consuming until TOKEN_EOF and aborts on the first sticky error so
the AST never contains noise after a fatal parse failure.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Creates the program root via create_cpp_ast_node(CPP_PROGRAM). Loop
peeks the cursor: TOKEN_EOF breaks. Branches by token kind to the
specialist parse_* routine; non-null child nodes are appended to the
program root via add_child_to_cpp_ast_node. After each iteration
has_parse_error is checked; on error the entire production is
discarded by returning 0 so the caller does not consume a half-built
tree. Returns the populated program node on clean EOF.
@End Implementation
Process called "parse_cpp_program" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse entire C++ program (top-level entry point)

    @Reasoning:
    Parse all top-level declarations including namespaces, classes, templates,
    functions, variables, and preprocessor directives until EOF is reached.
    Handle C++ specific constructs like using directives and template declarations.
    @End Reasoning

    Let program_node be proc create_cpp_ast_node from CPP_PROGRAM

    While 1 is equal to 1:
        Let token_type be proc peek_token_type from parser

        If token_type is equal to TOKEN_EOF from Lexer:
            Break
        End If

        Note: Parse namespace declaration
        If token_type is equal to TOKEN_NAMESPACE from Lexer:
            Let namespace_node be proc parse_namespace_declaration from parser
            If namespace_node is not equal to 0:
                proc add_child_to_cpp_ast_node with program_node, namespace_node
            End If
            Continue
        End If

        Note: Parse template declaration
        If token_type is equal to TOKEN_TEMPLATE from Lexer:
            Let template_node be proc parse_template_declaration from parser
            If template_node is not equal to 0:
                proc add_child_to_cpp_ast_node with program_node, template_node
            End If
            Continue
        End If

        Note: Parse class declaration
        If token_type is equal to TOKEN_CLASS from Lexer:
            Let class_node be proc parse_class_declaration from parser
            If class_node is not equal to 0:
                proc add_child_to_cpp_ast_node with program_node, class_node
            End If
            Continue
        End If

        Note: Parse struct declaration (treated as class with public default)
        If token_type is equal to TOKEN_STRUCT from Lexer:
            Let struct_node be proc parse_struct_declaration from parser
            If struct_node is not equal to 0:
                proc add_child_to_cpp_ast_node with program_node, struct_node
            End If
            Continue
        End If

        Note: Parse enum declaration
        If token_type is equal to TOKEN_ENUM from Lexer:
            Let enum_node be proc parse_enum_declaration from parser
            If enum_node is not equal to 0:
                proc add_child_to_cpp_ast_node with program_node, enum_node
            End If
            Continue
        End If

        Note: Parse using declaration/directive
        If token_type is equal to TOKEN_USING from Lexer:
            Let using_node be proc parse_using_declaration from parser
            If using_node is not equal to 0:
                proc add_child_to_cpp_ast_node with program_node, using_node
            End If
            Continue
        End If

        Note: Parse typedef declaration
        If token_type is equal to TOKEN_TYPEDEF from Lexer:
            Let typedef_node be proc parse_typedef_declaration from parser
            If typedef_node is not equal to 0:
                proc add_child_to_cpp_ast_node with program_node, typedef_node
            End If
            Continue
        End If

        Note: Parse preprocessor directives
        If token_type is equal to TOKEN_HASH from Lexer:
            Let preprocessor_node be proc parse_preprocessor_directive from parser
            If preprocessor_node is not equal to 0:
                proc add_child_to_cpp_ast_node with program_node, preprocessor_node
            End If
            Continue
        End If

        Note: Parse function or variable declaration
        Let declaration_node be proc parse_declaration from parser
        If declaration_node is not equal to 0:
            proc add_child_to_cpp_ast_node with program_node, declaration_node
        End If

        Let has_error be proc has_parse_error from parser

        If has_error is equal to 1:
            Return 0
        End If
    End While

    Return program_node
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Class Declaration Parsing
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning:
Parses 'class Name [<template-args>] [: base-list] { member-list }' or
'class Name;'. The class-access default is private (C++11 9.2/14
explicitly distinguishes class default-private from struct default-
public). Forward declarations short-circuit immediately on a semicolon
after the optional inheritance, distinguishing them from definitions.
The proc saves and restores parser.current_class to support nested
classes, where the inner class needs its own "this is the class being
parsed" context for constructor/destructor recognition.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Expects TOKEN_CLASS, creates a CPP_CLASS node, captures the identifier
into name. Optional template-arg list (TOKEN_LESS) and inheritance
(TOKEN_COLON) become child sub-trees. Semicolon -> forward-decl path
returns immediately. Otherwise '{' is expected; old_class is saved
from parser offset 32 and the new class node is stored there so
parse_class_member can identify constructors by name match.
current_access tracks default-private/protected/public via 0/1/2; each
access-specifier label flips it. Loop terminates on TOKEN_RBRACE.
Restores parser.current_class before returning the class node.
@End Implementation
Process called "parse_class_declaration" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse C++ class declaration with inheritance and access specifiers

    @Reasoning:
    Handle class declarations including inheritance lists, access specifiers,
    member functions, constructors, destructors, operator overloads, and nested classes.
    Support both declaration and definition forms.
    @End Reasoning

    proc expect_token with parser, TOKEN_CLASS from Lexer, "Expected 'class'"

    Let class_node be proc create_cpp_ast_node from CPP_CLASS

    Note: Parse class name
    Let class_name be proc peek_token_lexeme from parser
    proc expect_token with parser, TOKEN_IDENTIFIER from Lexer, "Expected class name"
    proc set_cpp_ast_node_name with class_node, class_name

    Note: Parse optional template specialization
    Let next_token be proc peek_token_type from parser
    If next_token is equal to TOKEN_LESS from Lexer:
        Let template_args be proc parse_template_argument_list from parser
        proc set_cpp_ast_node_template_params with class_node, template_args
    End If

    Note: Parse optional inheritance
    Let colon_token be proc peek_token_type from parser
    If colon_token is equal to TOKEN_COLON from Lexer:
        proc advance_token from parser  Note: consume ':'
        Let inheritance_list be proc parse_inheritance_list from parser
        proc add_child_to_cpp_ast_node with class_node, inheritance_list
    End If

    Note: Check for forward declaration vs definition
    Let brace_token be proc peek_token_type from parser
    If brace_token is equal to TOKEN_SEMICOLON from Lexer:
        Note: Forward declaration
        proc advance_token from parser
        Return class_node
    End If

    Note: Parse class body
    proc expect_token with parser, TOKEN_LBRACE from Lexer, "Expected '{' or ';'"

    Note: Set current class context for access control
    Let old_class be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with parser, 32
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with parser, 32, class_node

    Note: Default access is private for class
    Let current_access be 0  Note: 0 = private, 1 = protected, 2 = public

    While 1 is equal to 1:
        Let member_token be proc peek_token_type from parser

        If member_token is equal to TOKEN_RBRACE from Lexer:
            proc advance_token from parser
            Break
        End If

        Note: Parse access specifiers
        If member_token is equal to TOKEN_PUBLIC from Lexer:
            proc advance_token from parser
            proc expect_token with parser, TOKEN_COLON from Lexer, "Expected ':' after 'public'"
            Set current_access to 2
            Continue
        End If

        If member_token is equal to TOKEN_PRIVATE from Lexer:
            proc advance_token from parser
            proc expect_token with parser, TOKEN_COLON from Lexer, "Expected ':' after 'private'"
            Set current_access to 0
            Continue
        End If

        If member_token is equal to TOKEN_PROTECTED from Lexer:
            proc advance_token from parser
            proc expect_token with parser, TOKEN_COLON from Lexer, "Expected ':' after 'protected'"
            Set current_access to 1
            Continue
        End If

        Note: Parse member declaration
        Let member_node be proc parse_class_member with parser, current_access
        If member_node is not equal to 0:
            proc add_child_to_cpp_ast_node with class_node, member_node
        End If
    End While

    Note: Restore previous class context
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with parser, 32, old_class

    Return class_node
End Process

@Reasoning:
Dispatches a single member declaration inside a class body. Five
member kinds need bespoke handling because they cannot be reduced to
the generic parse_declaration path: constructor (identifier matching
the class name), destructor (TOKEN_TILDE), operator overload
(TOKEN_OPERATOR), friend (TOKEN_FRIEND), and template member
(TOKEN_TEMPLATE). The remainder falls through to parse_declaration.
Each path stamps access_level onto the produced node so later passes
can apply C++ access control without re-deriving the section context.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Reads the current_class handle from offset 32 and pulls its name for
constructor recognition. Peek-and-compare the cursor token against the
five special-case token kinds. For each special path, returns the
specialist's result directly so dispatch stays a single branch deep.
For template members, the produced node is stamped with the access
level only if it's non-null (graceful on inner parse failure). The
fallback parse_declaration also has its access_level stamped.
@End Implementation
Process called "parse_class_member" takes parser as Integer, access_level as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse class member (function, variable, constructor, destructor, etc.)

    @Reasoning:
    Handle all types of class members including member functions, data members,
    constructors, destructors, operator overloads, nested types, and friend declarations.
    Apply proper access level to each member.
    @End Reasoning

    Let token_type be proc peek_token_type from parser

    Note: Parse constructor (same name as class)
    Let current_class be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with parser, 32
    Let class_name be proc get_cpp_ast_node_name from current_class
    Let identifier_name be proc peek_token_lexeme from parser

    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_IDENTIFIER from Lexer:
        Let is_constructor be proc string_equals from StringCore with identifier_name, class_name

        If is_constructor is equal to 1:
            Return proc parse_constructor with parser, access_level
        End If

        Note: Check for destructor
        If token_type is equal to TOKEN_TILDE from Lexer:
            Return proc parse_destructor with parser, access_level
        End If
    End If

    Note: Parse operator overload
    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_OPERATOR from Lexer:
        Return proc parse_operator_overload with parser, access_level
    End If

    Note: Parse friend declaration
    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_FRIEND from Lexer:
        Return proc parse_friend_declaration with parser, access_level
    End If

    Note: Parse template member
    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_TEMPLATE from Lexer:
        Let template_member be proc parse_template_declaration from parser
        If template_member is not equal to 0:
            proc set_cpp_ast_node_access_level with template_member, access_level
        End If
        Return template_member
    End If

    Note: Parse regular member (function or variable)
    Let member_node be proc parse_declaration from parser
    If member_node is not equal to 0:
        proc set_cpp_ast_node_access_level with member_node, access_level
    End If

    Return member_node
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Template Declaration Parsing
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning:
Parses 'template <param-list> declaration'. The template parameter
list is itself a CPP_TEMPLATE_PARAM node containing child parameter
nodes; the templated declaration becomes a child of the template node.
template_depth is bumped before recursion so the lexer/parser can
disambiguate '>' as either greater-than or template close based on
nesting, then restored on exit to keep tracking accurate across
sibling templates.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Expects TOKEN_TEMPLATE; creates a CPP_TEMPLATE node. Reads the current
template_depth from offset 40, writes depth+1 back to track the open
angle bracket. Expects TOKEN_LESS. Creates a CPP_TEMPLATE_PARAM list
node, loops parse_template_parameter and appends, consuming optional
commas between entries; loop exits when peek returns TOKEN_GREATER
(which is also consumed). The collected param list is stored via
set_cpp_ast_node_template_params. Then parse_declaration recurses to
build the templated entity; its non-null result is appended as the
template body. Restores template_depth to the original value on exit.
@End Implementation
Process called "parse_template_declaration" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse template declaration with parameters and specializations

    @Reasoning:
    Handle template declarations including type parameters, non-type parameters,
    template template parameters, default arguments, and partial specializations.
    Support both function and class templates.
    @End Reasoning

    proc expect_token with parser, TOKEN_TEMPLATE from Lexer, "Expected 'template'"

    Let template_node be proc create_cpp_ast_node from CPP_TEMPLATE

    Note: Increment template depth for nested template tracking
    Let current_depth be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with parser, 40
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with parser, 40, current_depth plus 1

    Note: Parse template parameter list
    proc expect_token with parser, TOKEN_LESS from Lexer, "Expected '<' after 'template'"

    Let param_list be proc create_cpp_ast_node from CPP_TEMPLATE_PARAM

    While 1 is equal to 1:
        Let param_token be proc peek_token_type from parser

        If param_token is equal to TOKEN_GREATER from Lexer:
            proc advance_token from parser
            Break
        End If

        Note: Parse template parameter
        Let param_node be proc parse_template_parameter from parser
        If param_node is not equal to 0:
            proc add_child_to_cpp_ast_node with param_list, param_node
        End If

        Note: Check for comma separator
        Let comma_token be proc peek_token_type from parser
        If comma_token is equal to TOKEN_COMMA from Lexer:
            proc advance_token from parser
        End If
    End While

    proc set_cpp_ast_node_template_params with template_node, param_list

    Note: Parse the templated declaration
    Let templated_decl be proc parse_declaration from parser
    If templated_decl is not equal to 0:
        proc add_child_to_cpp_ast_node with template_node, templated_decl
    End If

    Note: Decrement template depth
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with parser, 40, current_depth

    Return template_node
End Process

@Reasoning:
Recognises the three template-parameter grammars from the C++ standard:
type parameter ('typename T' / 'class T'), non-type parameter
('int N'), and template template parameter ('template <...> class C').
The 'value' slot of the produced CPP_TEMPLATE_PARAM stores the
declarator keyword (TOKEN_TYPENAME / TOKEN_CLASS) so later passes can
discriminate without re-tokenising. Default-argument support is
handled inline: a trailing '= default-type' subtree is appended as a
child of the parameter node.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Branches by first token. TOKEN_TEMPLATE -> consume, recursively parse
a nested parameter list (template template parameter), expect
'class'/'typename', then identifier; build node and return.
TOKEN_TYPENAME -> consume, capture identifier, stamp value with
TOKEN_TYPENAME, optionally parse '= type-specifier'. TOKEN_CLASS
mirrors the TYPENAME path with TOKEN_CLASS as the value tag. Fallback:
delegate to parse_declaration for non-type parameters; this also
handles defaulted non-type params because parse_declaration recognises
the trailing '=' initialiser.
@End Implementation
Process called "parse_template_parameter" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse individual template parameter (type, non-type, or template template)

    @Reasoning:
    Handle three types of template parameters:
    1. Type parameters: typename T, class T
    2. Non-type parameters: int N, typename T::type* ptr
    3. Template template parameters: template<typename> class Container
    @End Reasoning

    Let param_token be proc peek_token_type from parser
    Let param_node be proc create_cpp_ast_node from CPP_TEMPLATE_PARAM

    Note: Template template parameter
    If param_token is equal to TOKEN_TEMPLATE from Lexer:
        proc advance_token from parser
        Let nested_params be proc parse_template_parameter_list from parser
        proc add_child_to_cpp_ast_node with param_node, nested_params

        Let class_token be proc peek_token_type from parser
        If class_token is equal to TOKEN_CLASS from Lexer:
            proc advance_token from parser
        Otherwise:
            proc expect_token with parser, TOKEN_TYPENAME from Lexer, "Expected 'class' or 'typename'"
        End If

        Let param_name be proc peek_token_lexeme from parser
        proc expect_token with parser, TOKEN_IDENTIFIER from Lexer, "Expected template template parameter name"
        proc set_cpp_ast_node_name with param_node, param_name

        Return param_node
    End If

    Note: Type parameter
    If param_token is equal to TOKEN_TYPENAME from Lexer:
        proc advance_token from parser
        Set param_name to proc peek_token_lexeme from parser
        proc expect_token with parser, TOKEN_IDENTIFIER from Lexer, "Expected type parameter name"
        proc set_cpp_ast_node_name with param_node, param_name
        proc set_cpp_ast_node_value with param_node, TOKEN_TYPENAME from Lexer

        Note: Parse optional default type
        Let equals_token be proc peek_token_type from parser
        If equals_token is equal to TOKEN_EQUALS from Lexer:
            proc advance_token from parser
            Let default_type be proc parse_type_specifier from parser
            proc add_child_to_cpp_ast_node with param_node, default_type
        End If

        Return param_node
    End If

    If param_token is equal to TOKEN_CLASS from Lexer:
        proc advance_token from parser
        Set param_name to proc peek_token_lexeme from parser
        proc expect_token with parser, TOKEN_IDENTIFIER from Lexer, "Expected type parameter name"
        proc set_cpp_ast_node_name with param_node, param_name
        proc set_cpp_ast_node_value with param_node, TOKEN_CLASS from Lexer

        Note: Parse optional default type
        Set equals_token to proc peek_token_type from parser
        If equals_token is equal to TOKEN_EQUALS from Lexer:
            proc advance_token from parser
            Set default_type to proc parse_type_specifier from parser
            proc add_child_to_cpp_ast_node with param_node, default_type
        End If

        Return param_node
    End If

    Note: Non-type parameter - parse as regular declaration
    Let non_type_decl be proc parse_declaration from parser
    Return non_type_decl
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Error Handling and Utility Functions
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning:
Sticky error setter used by every recursive-descent expectation. Stores
a parser-owned copy of the diagnostic so the caller's StringCore handle
is not aliased; the parser frees this copy in destroy_cpp_parser. Sets
the has_error flag so combinators can short-circuit instead of
producing a corrupt AST.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Writes has_error=1 at offset 24. Copies the supplied message via
StringCore.copy_string and stores the new handle at offset 16. If a
prior error_message existed, that slot is overwritten without an
explicit free; callers must only call set_parse_error once per parse
to avoid leaks, which is the recursive-descent contract here (sticky
flag prevents subsequent error reporting).
@End Implementation

@Security_Scope:
Message text is parser-internal; no untrusted input reaches this proc.
Length-bounded copy is provided by StringCore.copy_string.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "set_parse_error" takes parser as Integer, message as Integer:
    Note: Set parser error state with message

    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with parser, 24, 1  Note: has_error = true

    Let error_copy be proc copy_string from StringCore with message
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with parser, 16, error_copy
End Process

@Reasoning:
Sticky-flag accessor consumed by every parser combinator that branches on
success/failure. Returning the raw 0/1 lets callers also use it as a boolean
guard without an extra is_equal check.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Direct read of the has_error slot at offset 24. Constant-time.
@End Implementation

Process called "has_parse_error" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Check if parser has encountered an error

    Return proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with parser, 24
End Process

@Reasoning:
Names are user-controlled identifier text and are needed by every later
pass; the parser owns its own copy so the lexer's lexeme buffer can be
recycled. Defensive null-check on the node lets callers stay terse.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Null-checks node; otherwise copies the name StringCore via StringCore.copy_string
and stores the new handle at offset 8. The owning AST node frees the copy
when destroyed.
@End Implementation

Process called "set_cpp_ast_node_name" takes node as Integer, name as Integer:
    Note: Set AST node name

    If node is equal to 0:
        Return
    End If

    Let name_copy be proc copy_string from StringCore with name
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with node, 8, name_copy
End Process

@Reasoning:
The value slot holds operator strings ("+", "++", "->"), literal text, or
embedded auxiliary handles. Unlike name, value is stored BORROWED because
operator tokens are constant strings and literal text already lives on an
already-copied StringCore by the time the parser sets it.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Null-checks node and writes value handle at offset 16 verbatim. Caller is
responsible for ensuring value outlives the node, or for passing a freshly
copied StringCore.
@End Implementation

Process called "set_cpp_ast_node_value" takes node as Integer, value as Integer:
    Note: Set AST node value

    If node is equal to 0:
        Return
    End If

    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with node, 16, value
End Process

@Reasoning:
C++ class members are private/protected/public; the parser stamps the level
on each declaration so the semantic layer can enforce access rules without
re-walking back to the class scope.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Writes the access constant (ACCESS_PRIVATE/PROTECTED/PUBLIC from cpp_semantic)
into the attributes slot at offset 40. This slot is repurposed across node
kinds; the semantic layer interprets it according to node_type.
@End Implementation

Process called "set_cpp_ast_node_access_level" takes node as Integer, access as Integer:
    Note: Set access level for class member

    If node is equal to 0:
        Return
    End If

    Note: Store access level in attributes field
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with node, 40, access
End Process

@Reasoning:
Template parameter lists are parsed eagerly and attached to the template-
declaration node so HIR emission can specialise the template body against
those parameters at instantiation time.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Null-checks node and writes the parameter-list handle (a List of CppASTNode*
returned by parse_template_parameters) at offset 48. List ownership
transfers to the node.
@End Implementation

Process called "set_cpp_ast_node_template_params" takes node as Integer, params as Integer:
    Note: Set template parameters for node

    If node is equal to 0:
        Return
    End If

    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with node, 48, params
End Process

@Reasoning:
Read-only accessor for the node's owned name copy; returns 0 for null nodes
so visitor passes can chain accesses without null-checking the node first.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Null-check on node; otherwise returns the StringCore handle at offset 8.
Borrowed pointer - caller must not free.
@End Implementation

Process called "get_cpp_ast_node_name" takes node as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Get AST node name

    If node is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Return proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with node, 8
End Process